#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The information given in this section is not meant to be exhaustive. We provide\n"
"you with the settings Gentoo supports. If you use different settings we don't\n"
"say that Gentoo doesn't support it, but it is possible. We list the settings by\n"
"subarchitecture - a set of machine instructions supported by a range of x86\n"
"systems. All subarchitectures are derived from older, <e>compatible</e>\n"
"subarchitectures. If at any time you are uncertain which one to pick, you should\n"
"use the oldest subarchitecture. Picking one that is more recent than the one\n"
"your system supports will result in segmentation faults or internal errors.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>CXXFLAGS</c> setting is never shown, you should set it to the\n"
"<c>CFLAGS</c> one:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the CXXFLAGS variable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CFLAGS=\"...\"\n"
"<i>CXXFLAGS=\"${CFLAGS}\"</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "The generic x86 subarchitecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "The next settings work on every x86 system (apart from the i286 and lower):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generic x86 settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CHOST=\"i386-pc-linux-gnu\"\n"
"CFLAGS=\"-march=i386 -O2 -pipe\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "The ix86 series"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The ix86 series (i486, i586, i686) all refer to Intel- and Intel compatible\n"
"CPUs. The i586 instruction set is also known as the <e>Pentium</e> and the i686\n"
"one as the <e>Pentium Pro</e>, the predecessor of the <e>Pentium MMX</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "ix86 Series"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Substitute i486 with i586 or i686 accordingly)</comment>\n"
"CHOST=\"i486-pc-linux-gnu\"\n"
"CFLAGS=\"-march=i486 -O2 -pipe\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also substitute the <c>i486</c> value <e>inside the CFLAGS</e> setting\n"
"(and <e>not</e> the CHOST one) with <c>pentium</c> or\n"
"<c>pentium-pro</c> for such systems.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "Intel CPUs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:233
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additional support is available for various Intel CPUs, such as\n"
"<c>pentium-mmx</c>, <c>pentium2</c> (including Celeron), <c>pentium3</c>,\n"
"<c>pentium4</c>, and <c>nocona</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "Intel CPU series"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Substitute the pentium-mmx value in CFLAGS with the value you need)</comment>\n"
"CHOST=\"i686-pc-linux-gnu\"\n"
"CFLAGS=\"-march=pentium-mmx -O2 -pipe\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid "AMD CPUs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"AMD CPU users can use any of the following settings for <c>-march</c>:\n"
"<c>athlon-xp</c>, <c>athlon-mp</c>, <c>athlon-tbird</c>, <c>athlon</c>,\n"
"<c>k6</c>, <c>k6-2</c>, <c>k6-3</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "AMD CPU series"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Substitute the athlon-xp value in CFLAGS with the value you need)</comment>\n"
"CHOST=\"i686-pc-linux-gnu\"\n"
"CFLAGS=\"-march=athlon-xp -O2 -pipe\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:267
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bootloaders"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:269
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:273
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>grub</c> bootloader is a powerful application, able to boot various\n"
"operating systems, including Microsoft Windows. One of its most powerful\n"
"features is its ability to understand various file systems, which makes it\n"
"possible for <c>grub</c> to aide you in your boot setup, especially when there\n"
"are some issues you need to fix.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For instance, you can browse a file system looking for files, reading different\n"
"<c>grub</c> configurations, using various Linux kernels, locate files on the\n"
"system (and view their contents), but also hide partitions, boot from a network \n"
"using BOOTP (a simple file transfer protocol, very often used to send boot \n"
"images to various systems), change the partition table, ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:291
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB: configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:295
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To use <c>grub</c>, you need to install it first (from within the chrooted\n"
"environment):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing GRUB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge grub</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:304
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, edit (or create) the <path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path> file. \n"
"We'll first give you a simple example of a <path>grub.conf</path> file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example grub.conf file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"default 0\n"
"timeout 5\n"
"\n"
"title=Gentoo Linux\n"
"root (hd0,5)\n"
"kernel /kernel-2.6.14-gentoo-r2 root=/dev/sda8\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>grub</c> always starts counting from zero. For instance, to boot the first\n"
"entry by default, we state <c>default&nbsp;0</c>. The other line,\n"
"<c>timeout&nbsp;5</c>, tells GRUB to wait 5 seconds before it actually boots the\n"
"entry pointed to by the <c>default</c> setting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:325
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is of course not the most difficult part of GRUB. The entries themselves\n"
"however are. In the given example, there are three commands given to GRUB:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ol><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <c>title</c> entry tells GRUB what to display to the user when he is\n"
"    asked to make his selection.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ol><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <c>root</c> entry informs GRUB where its own files are stored. This is\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ol><li><brite>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid "not"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ol><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" the Linux root file system (it can be, but this isn't\n"
"    always true). If you have <path>/boot</path> (where GRUB stores its files)\n"
"    as a separate partition, you point this directive to that partition.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ol><li>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:341
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <c>kernel</c> entry is used by GRUB to know what Linux kernel to boot\n"
"    (relative to the file system where <c>root</c> points to) and what boot\n"
"    parameters to add.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Many users often make a mistake when they configure the <c>root</c> parameter.\n"
"That's mostly because the syntax used by GRUB to identify partitions is\n"
"different from what they're used to work with. Its syntax is quite simple:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUBs partition syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "(hd<i>harddisk-#</i>,<i>partition-#</i>)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>harddisk-#</c> is the hard disk number, starting from 0. If you only have\n"
"one hard disk, it is <c>0</c>, regardless of where the disk is at. If you have\n"
"several disks, start counting from the one which your system checks first. For\n"
"instance, if you only have IDE disks, your system will probably start with the\n"
"primary master, then primary slave, then secundary master, ... \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:366
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>partition-#</c> is the partition number, starting from 0, and uses the\n"
"same logic used with the partitioning you did earlier. The first four partitions\n"
"(0-3) are the primary partitions. The logical partitions start from the number\n"
"4. So, in the above example, the GRUB files are stored on the second logical\n"
"partition on the first disk (also known as <path>/dev/sda6</path>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You'll find more information about GRUB (including nicely commented\n"
"configuration examples) in the GRUB info pages:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "Retrieving GRUB information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>info grub</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:385
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB: installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You still have to install <c>grub</c> in the MBR (Master Boot Record) though, so\n"
"that your BIOS is able to find and start it. Otherwise, your system will inform\n"
"you that no operating system is found...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:395
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The recommended method uses <c>grub-install</c> to setup GRUB. Yet this tool\n"
"relies on some information not present on your system yet: the\n"
"<path>/etc/mtab</path> file, a cache file which contains information about the\n"
"mounted file systems. Create one that makes <c>grub-install</c> happy, you only\n"
"need to enter the file system for your root partition (<path>/</path>) and, if\n"
"you have one, for your boot partition (<path>/boot</path>):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:403
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example /etc/mtab file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/dev/sda8   /       ext3   rw,noatime   0 0\n"
"/dev/sda6   /boot   ext2   rw,noatime   0 0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then, run <c>grub-install</c> with the device that resembles your first\n"
"disk that the system will boot. For instance, if that first disk is\n"
"<path>/dev/sda</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing GRUB in the MBR using grub-install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(grub-install also supports the (hd0) notation)</comment>\n"
"# <i>grub-install /dev/sda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>grub-install</c> tool will then search through <path>/etc/mtab</path> to\n"
"find out where the GRUB files are stored and install a minimal boot loader in\n"
"the MBR whose only job is to find and start the rest of the GRUB files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:426
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you come to the conclusion that the installation has failed, you can try to\n"
"perform the <c>grub-install</c> steps manually. Run <c>grub</c>, then enter the\n"
"configuration commands <c>root</c> (where are the GRUB files located - same as \n"
"the one in the configuration file <path>grub.conf</path>),  <c>setup</c> (where \n"
"to install GRUB - <path>(hd0)</path> is most likely) and <c>quit</c> (to exit \n"
"the GRUB installation):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:434
#, no-wrap
msgid "Performing the GRUB installation steps manually"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/draft/complete/hb-app_arch-x86.xml:435
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(The following is just an example)</comment>\n"
"# <i>grub</i>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>root (hd0,5)</i>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>setup (hd0)</i>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>quit</i>\n"
msgstr ""
